#19601
The Ribcage Cathedral~
   You have entered the skeletal cathedral of the fallen god. Towering
ribs, curved like mountain ranges, arch overhead to form a vaulted 
ceiling miles above your head. The floor is a carpet of pulverized 
bone dust that crunches softly beneath your boots. The space is 
illuminated by massive geodes bursting from the stone walls, their 
crystals pulsing with a rhythmic, magical energy. High up on the 
vertebrae, you spot scavengers with crystalline carapaces darting
between the bones, their movements silent and predatory. The sheer 
scale of this place makes you feel insignificant, like an ant 
crawling upon a corpse.
~
